702608f-d.text:
(1)
8024-8200 Eighteenth Ave., west side, north of 82nd Street, showing from left to right Nos. 8200, 8112, and 8024. The house, No. 8024, was (in 1873) the home of Mrs. Wardell. It was at the N.W. corner of 81st Street. Now (1929) the Bensonhurst Garden Apartments occupy the site. No. 8112 was the home of the Revs. Dr. J. and H.S. Carpenter in 1860 and 1873, respectively. In 1929 a row of 2-story dwellings was on the s ite. No. 8200 which was the home of John C. Bennett, still stands in 1929. It will be demolished at some future date for the continuation of 82nd
Street.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing the home of the Drs. Carpenter.
1922.
Eugene L, Armbruster Collection.
